text.section:
The Institution shall have the following staff:
two associate directors, one of whom is a competent psychiatrist with at least 3 years of experience in the practice or teaching of psychiatry and one of whom is a competent behavioral scientist with at least 3 years of experience in the practice or teaching of the individual's specialty in behavioral science;
a warden;
at least three additional psychiatrists or clinical psychologists;
at least four State licensed certified social workers-clinical; and
other professional and nonprofessional staff, as provided in the State budget.

section.section:
With the approval of the Secretary, the Director shall appoint an individual to any position that the Secretary determines to be professional, including:
each associate director;
each social worker;
each sociologist;
each physician; and
each psychologist.
